Maintainer: Fernando Machado-Stredel <f.machado.stredel@gmail.com>
Date: 2023-12-06
Description: 
    A set of tools to perform simulations based on considerations of 
    Grinnellian ecological niches and other user-defined dispersal paramaters.
    Dispersal simulations can be performed under constant or changing 
    environmental conditions (distinct scenarios of suitability). The main
    results that can be obtained using these simulations include accessible 
    areas and colonized areas. Considerations of accessible areas in the tools 
    included are particularly novel compared to similar packages.
    Theoretical and methodological bases for the approaches and tools 
    implemented can be found in:
    Machado-Stredel et al. (2021) <doi:10.21425/F5FBG48814>,
    Barve et al. (2011) <doi:10.1016/j.ecolmodel.2011.02.011>,
    Nunez et al. (2021) <doi:10.21425/F5FBG52142>,
    Peterson et al. (1999) <doi:10.1126/science.285.5431.1265>,
    Peterson et al. (2011) <https://www.degruyter.com/princetonup/view/title/506966>,
    Soberon and Peterson (2005) <doi:10.17161/bi.v2i0.4>,
    Soberon and Peterson (2020) <doi:10.1007/s12080-019-0432-5>.
